      <block class="full_text">
        <p>* Cole-Haan Inc., Yarmouth, Me., to Margeotes Fertitta &amp; Weiss, New York, from Cipriani-Kremer, Boston. The review for the shoe company's $4.5 million wholesale account included Bozell Inc., Deutsch Inc. and McCaffrey &amp; McCall Inc., all of New York.</p>
        <p>* Slater Hanft &amp; Martin, New York, has been invited to participate in a review for the estimated $5 million Channel Home Centers account, competing against Christopher Thomas Associates, Garden City, L.I., and three New York agencies: Lord, Dentsu &amp; Partners; Margeotes Fertitta &amp; Weiss, and Rosenfeld, Sirowitz, Humphrey &amp; Strauss.</p>
